# Claude Code Rules for pptx-slide-copier

## Git Workflow Rules

### NEVER push directly to main branch
- All changes MUST go through the Pull Request workflow
- Before any `git push`, verify the current branch is NOT main
- If on main branch, create a new feature branch first

### Always follow this workflow:
1. Create a new branch: `git checkout -b <descriptive-branch-name>`
2. Make changes and commit
3. Push to remote: `git push -u origin <branch-name>`
4. Create a Pull Request using `gh pr create`

### Branch Naming Convention
- Use descriptive kebab-case names
- Examples: `add-feature-x`, `fix-bug-y`, `update-documentation`

### Before pushing, always check:
```bash
git branch --show-current
```
- If output is "main", STOP and create a new branch

## Code Quality Rules

### Before committing:
- Run linter: `ruff check .`
- Run tests: `pytest tests/ -v`
- Fix any errors before committing

### Commit Message Format
- Use clear, descriptive commit messages
- End with Claude Code attribution:
  ```
  ðŸ¤– Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)

  Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
  ```

## Python Development Rules

### Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 conventions
- Line length: 120 characters (configured in pyproject.toml)
- Use type hints where appropriate

### Testing
- Write tests for new features
- Ensure all tests pass before creating PR
- Maintain test coverage

## Documentation Rules

### Only create documentation when explicitly requested
- Do not proactively create README or markdown files
- Update existing documentation when changes affect usage

## Package Management

### PyPI Publishing
- Never publish to PyPI without explicit user confirmation
- Always test with TestPyPI first if available
- Verify version number before publishing
